After a renowned American journalist Seymour Hersh broke the news that the U.S. is the backstage manipulator of Nord Stream sabotage who had schemed to destroy Russia's pipelines a few days ago. Phinij Jarusombat, former Thai Deputy Prime Minister, pointed out the U.S. is the biggest beneficiary and the main suspect behind the Nord Stream attack. "No matter who blew up the Nord Stream gas pipeline, their motives are full of malice.This has seriously affected the normal life of European people. (The U.S.) keeps creating conflict in order to maintain its own world hegemony," said Phinij Jarusombat during an interview with China Media Group.